# Project document rules (ISS)

Applies whenever you **create, move, rename, or reference** handover notes, ADRs, or registry files.

## 1) Locations (repo root)

| Kind | Path |
| --- | --- |
| Handover, QA notes, async questions | `handover/` |
| Architecture Decision Records (ADR) | **`adr/`** (at repository root — not under `design-book/`) |
| Canonical indexes (pointers only) | `registry/` |

## 2) One ADR index

- **Only** `registry/adr-registry.md` lists ADRs for humans and agents.
- When you add an ADR file, **update that registry** in the same change (or immediately after).

## 3) Naming — `handover/`

Pattern (required for every new file):

`YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS-<ROLE>-<short-slug>.md`

- Date and time: **UTC+8**, 24-hour clock, **include seconds** (`HHMMSS`).
- `<ROLE>`: `QAC`, `Dev`, `UXI`, `PDM`, `ARC` (extend only if the team agrees).
- `<short-slug>`: kebab-case, short, no spaces.

Example: `20260417-143022-QAC-login-flow-regression.md`

## 4) Naming — `adr/`

Same pattern as handover:

`YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS-<ROLE>-<short-slug>.md`

Example: `20260416-153000-ARC-use-root-adr-folder.md`

## 5) Naming — `registry/`

Use **stable** filenames (no timestamps in the name), e.g. `adr-registry.md`, so links stay valid.

## 6) Approved docs

- Do not edit or delete **approved** specs without explicit user confirmation (see `global-rules.mdc`).
